{
  "_README": "Canonical, repo-owned BACKUP_COPY JobDto skeleton. Unlike flb_job.template.json/fsb_job.template.json (which back up a LIVE source), a Backup Copy (BC) job copies an EXISTING backup object into a second, different repository — its sourceVid is a BACKUP_OBJECT, not a discovery/source VID. Runbooks build a NEW job from THIS file (recipe R4d), never by cloning a live/golden BC job. Substitution contract: __JOB_NAME__, objects[0].sourceVid=__SOURCE_BACKUP_OBJECT_VID__ (an EXISTING BACKUP_OBJECT-<id>, e.g. produced by an AUTO_FLB_* job), objects[0].targetName=__SOURCE_NAME__ (that backup object's display name), objects[0].targetStorageVid=__TARGET_REPO_VID__ (must differ from the source backup object's own repo). IMPORTANT: top-level hvType is a FIXED 'VMWARE' — NOT the source object's own hvType. VERIFIED 2026-07-07 nbr-84: a Backup Copy job built via saveJob with hvType='PHYSICAL' (matching an FLB/PHYSICAL/FILE_LEVEL source) failed immediately at run time with FeatureNotSupportedException (BackupCopyEnforcePreconditions) — see job 34 in test-data/test-data.md §4. A job created through the Director UI for the SAME FLB source came back with hvType:'VMWARE' at the top level and ran successfully (job 35, lrState:OK, real savepoints copied) — the UI wizard's URL even defaults to hv=VMWARE before any source is picked, regardless of what you select. So hvType='VMWARE' is a fixed, generic value BC jobs require irrespective of the actual source's hvType; do not parametrize it. Remove the _README/_SUBSTITUTION keys before saveJob.",
